# COPR repositories to enable before installing packages.
#
# Fedora analogue of the Chaotic-AUR / AUR usage in awzmlinux
# (extensions/post_bootstrap.sh + post_install.sh on Arch).
#
# Format: one `owner/project` per line. Enabled with `dnf copr enable -y` in the
# post_bootstrap extension. Comment out any you don't need. These are common
# sources for the packages marked "COPR" in package.list; adjust to taste.

# Hyprland ecosystem (only needed if not in the main Fedora repos for your release)
# solopasha/hyprland

# keyd key remapping daemon (if not in stable Fedora repos)
# alternateved/keyd

# kmscon terminal
# atim/kmscon

# Niche tooling
# firecracker -> upstream release binary, see extensions/post_install.sh notes
